## One thing still needed: git remote

The repo has no remote. Once Ewing sets up the GitHub repo, run:

```bash
cd ~/Projects/master-crm-web
git remote add origin https://github.com/ewing-operating-system/master-crm-web.git
git push -u origin main
```

After that, `scripts/regenerate.py` will auto-push and Vercel will deploy on every run.

---

## One known issue: `RESEARCHED` enum value

`pipeline_status` is a PostgreSQL enum. The `RESEARCHED` value doesn't exist yet — when the research agent sets that status, it will need to be added to the DB enum first:

```sql
ALTER TYPE pipeline_status ADD VALUE 'RESEARCHED';
```

Until then, `regenerate.py` falls back cleanly to Condition B (research_completed_at IS NOT NULL + report_generated_at IS NULL).

---

## How to run

```bash
# Dry run (safe preview):
python3 scripts/regenerate.py --dry-run

# One company:
python3 scripts/regenerate.py --company "AquaScience"

# Full rebuild (all 171 targets):
python3 scripts/regenerate_all.py

# Full rebuild for next_chapter only:
python3 scripts/regenerate_all.py --entity next_chapter
```
